The paper focuses on the development of a methodology for fast prototyping and learning of robot locomotion, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also emphasized in the paper. The paper also discusses the use of sample-efficient learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The study involves the design and testing of a crawling robot, which involves the use of control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) for navigation and obstacle avoidance.
